poses or public use regulations.  See 15USC§3710a(b)(1)(B)',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(4,0,1,'Performance','',4,'Multiple Collaborators','Multi Collab Text2','Statutory requirement.  ICD must ensure that the government retains specific rights; i.e., ICD requires the Collaborator to grant licenses for specific health and safety purposes or public use regulations.  See 15USC§3710a(b)(1)(B)',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(4,0,2,'Definitions','',4,'default','<B> Research Plan</B>: “Research Plan” means the statement in Appendix A of the respective research and development commitments of the Parties.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:38:08',NULL),(4,0,3,'Definitions','',4,'default','<B> Research Plan</B>: “Research Plan” means the statement in Appendix A of the respective research and development commitments of the Parties.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-06 14:15:47',NULL),(4,0,4,'Definitions','',4,'default','<B> Research Plan</B>: “Research Plan” means the statement in Appendix A of the respective research and development commitments of the Parties.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'all-user','2015-01-06 17:55:54',NULL),(5,0,1,'Performance','',5,'default','Any {Collaborator} employees who will work at {ICD} facilities will be required to sign an appropriate agreement in view of the terms of this CRADA.','optional language for use when Collaborator employee will be working at ICD.  There is currently no official PHS guest researcher or special volunteer agreement that is specific for CRADAs.  Consult OGC if Collaborator asks for a specific agreement to be included as an Appendix.',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(5,0,2,'Definitions','',5,'default','<B> Invention</B>: \"Invention\" means any invention, whether or not covered by a patent or patent application, or discovery which is or may be patentable or otherwise protectable under Title 35 of the United States Code, the Plant Variety Protection Act, 7 U.S.C. §§ 2321 et seq. or foreign patent law.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:38:08',NULL),(5,0,3,'Definitions','',5,'default','<B> Invention</B>: \"Invention\" means any invention, whether or not covered by a patent or patent application, or discovery which is or may be patentable or otherwise protectable under Title 35 of the United States Code, the Plant Variety Protection Act, 7 U.S.C. §§ 2321 et seq. or foreign patent law.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-06 14:15:47',NULL),(5,0,4,'Definitions','',5,'default','<B> Invention</B>: \"Invention\" means any invention, whether or not covered by a patent or patent application, or discovery which is or may be patentable or otherwise protectable under Title 35 of the United States Code, the Plant Variety Protection Act, 7 U.S.C. §§ 2321 et seq. or foreign patent law.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'all-user','2015-01-06 17:55:54',NULL),(6,0,1,'Performance','',6,'default','The Parties agree to use Collaborator Materials and ICD Materials in accordance with activities described under the Research Plan.  The Parties further agree to retain control over these materials and will not transfer these materials to third parties, without advance written approval of the providing Party.  Upon expiration or termination of the CRADA, each Party agrees to dispose of these materials as directed by the owning or providing Party.','This is standard language that would be used in any MTA.  This is good business practice.  This is a good starting point for negotiations but may be modified as needed to fit the needs of the IC and Collaborator to carry out the Research Plan.  Optional--to add -- \"Upon notice of termination, the Parties will devise a plan for sharing and distribution of CRADA Materials and CRADA Data.\" If you anticipate creating CRADA Materials (such as mice, antibodies, etc), this sentence may used as a starting point for negotiations so that you don\'t have to settle the plan before you even know the value of the CRADA Materials or CRADA Data.',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(6,0,2,'Definitions','',6,'default','<B> Affiliate</B>: “Affiliate” means any corporation or other business entity controlled by, controlling, or under common control with Collaborator at any time during the term of the CRADA.  For this purpose, “control” means direct or indirect beneficial ownership of at least fifty percent (50%) of the voting stock or at least fifty percent (50%) interest in the income of the corporation or other business entity.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:38:08',NULL),(6,0,3,'Definitions','',6,'default','<B> Affiliate</B>: “Affiliate” means any corporation or other business entity controlled by, controlling, or under common control with Collaborator at any time during the term of the CRADA.  For this purpose, “control” means direct or indirect beneficial ownership of at least fifty percent (50%) of the voting stock or at least fifty percent (50%) interest in the income of the corporation or other business entity.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-06 14:15:47',NULL),(6,0,4,'Definitions','',6,'default','<B> Affiliate</B>: “Affiliate” means any corporation or other business entity controlled by, controlling, or under common control with Collaborator at any time during the term of the CRADA.  For this purpose, “control” means direct or indirect beneficial ownership of at least fifty percent (50%) of the voting stock or at least fifty percent (50%) interest in the income of the corporation or other business entity.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'all-user','2015-01-06 17:55:54',NULL),(7,0,1,'Performance','',7,'default','This CRADA shall be effective upon execution by the Parties and will be in force for the term set forth on the Summary Page. The term may be extended and the provisions of this CRADA may be modified only by amendment signed by the duly authorized signatory for each Party. This Agreement may be terminated by either Party for any reason by providing written notice at least thirty (30) days prior to the desired termination date.','All CRADAs must have a term limit and will not be approved without one. It is preferable by NIH that the term be specified in the Summary Page, but if requested by the Collaborator, the actual term can be added to this clause.  For example, the first sentence could say \"This CRADA shall be effective upon execution by the Parties and will be in force for the term of X years.\"  CRADAs typically have a term of 1-5 years.  You should consider using the upper limit for the term to avoid amendments if possible and agreeable by the Collaborator.  It is easier to terminate than to amend.  Under NIH Policy, the CRADA can only be extended or modified by formal amendment and therefore the second sentence is required.  It is good business practice to address termination and therefore the last sentence is strongly recommended.',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(7,0,2,'Definitions','',7,'default','<B> Government</B>: “Government” means the Government of the United States of America.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:38:08',NULL),(7,0,3,'Definitions','',7,'default','<B> Government</B>: “Government” means the Government of the United States of America.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-06 14:15:47',NULL),(7,0,4,'Definitions','',7,'default','<B> Government</B>: “Government” means the Government of the United States of America.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'all-user','2015-01-06 17:55:54',NULL),(8,0,1,'Performance','',8,'default','Any dispute arising under this CRADA which is not disposed of by agreement of the Principal Investigators will be submitted jointly to the signatories of this CRADA.  If the signatories, or their designees, are unable to jointly resolve the dispute within thirty (30) days after notification thereof, the Assistant Secretary for Health (or his/her designee or successor) will propose a resolution.  Nothing in this paragraph will prevent any Party from pursuing any additional administrative remedies that may be available and, after exhaustion of such administrative remedies, pursuing all available judicial remedies.  Pending the resolution of any dispute or claim pursuant to this Article, the Parties agree that performance of all obligations will be pursued diligently.','This section is not statutory. However, it is good business practice to include how disputes will be resolved.  This language is a good point for starting negotiations and is recommended by OGC.  If Collaborator request changes, please be aware that some language is not allowed as a Federal Entity.  *Note that a common, unacceptable modification requested by companies is the following:  “ICD recognizes and agrees that there is no adequate remedy at law for any breach of its obligations hereunder…” Switching this statement to read:  “ICD recognizes and agrees that there MAY BE no adequate remedy at law for any breach of its obligations hereunder…” makes this acceptable.  Companies also commonly request that ICD agree to provide “equitable relief” or “judicial relief” in advance.  This is unacceptable; we may not agree to a specific remedy in advance.  Department of Justice (DOJ) is responsible for litigating cases for ICD.',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(8,0,2,'Definitions','',8,'default','<B> Effective Date</B>: “Effective Date” means the date of the last signature of the Parties executing this Agreement.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:38:08',NULL),(8,0,3,'Definitions','',8,'default','<B> Effective Date</B>: “Effective Date” means the date of the last signature of the Parties executing this Agreement.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-06 14:15:47',NULL),(8,0,4,'Definitions','',8,'default','<B> Effective Date</B>: “Effective Date” means the date of the last signature of the Parties executing this Agreement.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'all-user','2015-01-06 17:55:54',NULL),(9,0,1,'Performance','',9,'default','Except as specifically stated herein, the Parties make no express or implied warranty as to any matter whatsoever, including the conditions of the research or any invention or material, made or developed under or outside the scope of this CRADA, or the ownership, merchant ability, or fitness for a particular purpose of the research or any invention or any invention or material, or that a technology utilized by a party in the performance of the research plan does not infringe any third-party patent rights.','This is required.  It is universal language that almost never has request for changes. If Collaborator request changes, please consult OGC.',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(9,0,2,'Definitions','',9,'default','<B> Confidential Information</B>: “Confidential Information” means confidential scientific, business, or financial information provided by either Party to the other Party that is necessary to conduct the activities of the Research Plan. Confidential Information does not include the following:   \n(a) information that is or becomes publicly known or that is available from public sources; \n(b) information that has been made available by its owner to others without a confidentiality obligation; \n(c) information that is already known by the receiving Party, or information that is independently created or compiled by the receiving Party, without reference to or use of the provided information; or\n(d) information that relates to potential hazards or cautionary warnings associated with the production, handling, or use of the subject matter of the Research Plan; or  \n(e) CRADA Data, descriptions of CRADA Materials, or IPI, which have separate confidentiality obligations as described in Article 8.6.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:38:08',NULL),(9,0,3,'Definitions','',9,'default','<B> Confidential Inf