ADA Materials, or IPI, which have separate confidentiality obligations as described in Article 8.6.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'all-user','2015-01-06 17:55:54',NULL),(10,0,1,'Performance','',10,'default','No indemnification for any loss, claim, or liability is intended or provided by any Party under this Agreement.  Each Party will be liable for any claims or damages it incurs in connection with this CRADA, except that {ICD}, as an agency of the Government, assumes liability only to the extent provided under the Federal Tort Claims Act , 28 U.S.C. Chapter 171.','Limitation of Indemnification is governed by statutory requirements under 31 U.S.C. § 1341 Anti-Deficiency Act and by the Federal Tort Claims Act, 28 U.S.C. Chapter 171.  This language is recommended as the starting point for negotiations because it the most friendly to Collaborator.  However, other language that has been approved by OGC may be used, including:  \"It is the intention of ICD that Collaborator not be liable to ICD for any claims or damages arising from ICD\'s use of the Research Material; however no indemnification is provided or intended.\"  ',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(10,0,2,'Definitions','',10,'default','<B> Agreement</B>: undefined',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:38:08',NULL),(10,0,3,'Definitions','',10,'default','<B> Agreement</B>: undefined',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-06 14:15:47',NULL),(10,0,4,'Definitions','',10,'default','<B> Agreement</B>: undefined',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'all-user','2015-01-06 17:55:54',NULL),(11,0,1,'Performance','',11,'default','Neither Party will be liable for any unforeseeable event beyond its reasonable control and not caused by its own fault or negligence, which causes the Party to be unable to perform its obligations under this CRADA, and which it has been unable to overcome by the exercise of due diligence.  If a force majeure event occurs, the Party unable to perform will promptly notify the other Party.  It will use its best efforts to resume performance as quickly as possible and will suspend performance only for such period of time as is necessary as a result of the force majeure event.','it is strongly recommended that this language be included.  If Collaborator request that the language be deleted, then consult with OGC.  It is rare that Collaborators request changes to this language since it is fairly innocuous.',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(11,0,2,'Definitions','',11,'default','<B> CRADA Data</B>: “CRADA Data” means all recorded information first produced in the performance of the Research Plan.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:38:08',NULL),(11,0,3,'Definitions','',11,'default','<B> CRADA Data</B>: “CRADA Data” means all recorded information first produced in the performance of the Research Plan.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-06 14:15:47',NULL),(11,0,4,'Definitions','',11,'default','<B> CRADA Data</B>: “CRADA Data” means all recorded information first produced in the performance of the Research Plan.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'all-user','2015-01-06 17:55:54',NULL),(12,0,1,'Performance','',12,'default','If {Collaborator} elects to perform a portion of the Research Plan through a third party (e.g. as a contractor of {Collaborator}), {Collaborator} agrees to notify {ICD} and to ensure that the agreement between {Collaborator} and the third party will be consistent with {Collaborator}’s obligation under this CRADA. In particular, to the extent any Invention the third party may make would be a CRADA Subject Invention, any such Invention shall thereafter be treated as a CRADA Subject Invention in all respects.','This language is optional.  Use this language only if Collaborator has 3rd party contractors which may retain IP rights.  If you anticipate that a contractor may be used at any point during the CRADA then this language should be used.  ','If Collaborator uses contractors, then under statutes [15USC§3710a(b) ], the government must retain certain rights to CRADA Subject Inventions under the CRADA.',0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(12,0,2,'Definitions','',12,'default','<B> CRADA Materials</B>: “CRADA Materials” means all tangible materials first produced in the performance of the Research Plan.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:38:08',NULL),(12,0,3,'Definitions','',12,'default','<B> CRADA Materials</B>: “CRADA Materials” means all tangible materials first produced in the performance of the Research Plan.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-06 14:15:47',NULL),(12,0,4,'Definitions','',12,'default','<B> CRADA Materials</B>: “CRADA Materials” means all tangible materials first produced in the performance of the Research Plan.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'all-user','2015-01-06 17:55:54',NULL),(13,0,1,'Performance','',13,'default','If {ICD} elects to perform a portion of the Research Plan through a third party (e.g. as a contractor of the {ICD}), {ICD} agrees to notify {Collaborator}. However, {Collaborator} acknowledges that it is aware that under the Bayh-Dole Act (35 U.S.C. Part 2, Chapter 19) the third party may retain title to any Invention it makes in the performance of its duties despite the fact that the Government supported the work, and consequently, {ICD} has no authority to make such an Invention subject to the terms of this CRADA. However, {Collaborator} may enter into a  separate agreement with the third party regarding this agreement, provided however that the separate agreement does not contradict the terms of this Agreement or the third party’s  agreement  with {ICD}.  ','This language is optional.  Use this language only use if ICD has 3rd party contractors which may retain IP rights .  If you anticipate that a contractor may be used at any point during the CRADA then this language should be used.  See alternate language if contractors are under a DEC.',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(13,0,2,'Definitions','',13,'default','<B> Identifiable Private Information</B>: “Identifiable Private Information” or “IPI” means …',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:38:08',NULL),(13,0,3,'Definitions','',13,'default','<B> Identifiable Private Information</B>: “Identifiable Private Information” or “IPI” means …',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-06 14:15:47',NULL),(13,0,4,'Definitions','',13,'default','<B> Identifiable Private Information</B>: “Identifiable Private Information” or “IPI” means …',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'all-user','2015-01-06 17:55:54',NULL),(14,0,1,'Performance','',14,'default','If {ICD} elects to perform a portion of the Research Plan through a third party (e.g. as a contractor of the {ICD}), {ICD} agrees to notify {Collaborator}. {ICD}’s contractor is subject to a Determination of Exceptional Circumstances [“DEC”, 35 U.S.C. Sec. 202(a) (ii)]. Through the DEC, rights in CRADA Subject Inventions made during the term of the contract are assigned to {ICD} by the {ICD}’s contractor and are thereby subject to the licensing terms  within  this CRADA.','This language is optional.  Use this language only use if ICD has 3rd party contractors under DEC.  If you anticipate that a contractor may be used at any point during the CRADA then this language should be used if the contractors are under a DEC. Only a few contractors are under a DEC, please ask your PI or TDC to determine if this applies under your CRADA.  See alternate language if contractors are not under a DEC.',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(14,0,2,'Definitions','',14,'default','<B> Letter of Intent</B>: undefined',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:38:08',NULL),(14,0,3,'Definitions','',14,'default','<B> Letter of Intent</B>: undefined',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-06 14:15:47',NULL),(14,0,4,'Definitions','',14,'default','<B> Letter of Intent</B>: undefined',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'all-user','201