',NULL),(21,0,1,'Performance','',21,'default','{Collaborator} will provide funds in accordance with the performance of the Research Plan.  {Collaborator} will make payments according to payment schedule set forth below.   If {Collaborator} fails to make any scheduled payment, {ICD} will not be obligated to carry out research and development activities until funds have been received.    {Collaborator} agrees to provide funds in the amount of $X per year in support of the CRADA for {ICD}\'s use to acquire technical, statistical, and administrative support for the research activities, as well as to pay for supplies and travel expenses.  {Collaborator} will provide funds in (Y) equal annual installments for a total of $X.  The first installment of $X will be due within thirty (30) days of the Effective Date.  Each subsequent installment of $X will be due within thirty (30) days of each anniversary of the Effective Date.  {Collaborator} agrees that {ICD} can allocate the funding between the various categories in support of the CRADA as {ICD}’s PI sees fit using best scientific and business judgment.                   CRADA PAYMENTS:\n{Collaborator} has three options for making CRADA payments.  \nOption 1:  {Collaborator} sends checks to the {ICD}.\nOption 2:  {Collaborator} makes payments to {ICD} via wire transfer.\nOption 3:  {Collaborator} makes payments to {ICD} using www.pay.gov.\n{Collaborator} acknowledges that {ICD} will have the authority to retain and use any funds in the event of expiration or termination to cover costs associated with the conduct of activities  described under the Research Plan that were initiated prior to expiration or termination.','Optional when funds are provided to conduct activities under the Research Plan.  The language provided is just an example or guideline.  NOTE:  Under CRADA statutes, CRADA funds can only be used as specified in the CRADA, so  it is important to address this point. [ link to §3710 (b) 3].   Funds can not be used 