hin thirty (30) days of each anniversary of the Effective Date.  {Collaborator} agrees that {ICD} can allocate the funding between the various categories in support of the CRADA as {ICD}’s PI sees fit using best scientific and business judgment.                   CRADA PAYMENTS:\n{Collaborator} has three options for making CRADA payments.  \nOption 1:  {Collaborator} sends checks to the {ICD}.\nOption 2:  {Collaborator} makes payments to {ICD} via wire transfer.\nOption 3:  {Collaborator} makes payments to {ICD} using www.pay.gov.\n{Collaborator} acknowledges that {ICD} will have the authority to retain and use any funds in the event of expiration or termination to cover costs associated with the conduct of activities  described under the Research Plan that were initiated prior to expiration or termination.','Optional when funds are provided to conduct activities under the Research Plan.  The language provided is just an example or guideline.  NOTE:  Under CRADA statutes, CRADA funds can only be used as specified in the CRADA, so  it is important to address this point. [ link to §3710 (b) 3].   Funds can not be used to hire or pay an FTE employee. Advice is to use broad language and be sure that the language is included.  Examples of broad language that can be used include \"use to acquire technical, statistical, and administrative support for the research activities, as well as to pay for supplies and travel expenses\" and \"Collaborator agrees that ICD can allocate the funding between the various categories in support of the CRADA research as ICD’s PI sees fit using best scientific and business judgment.\" and should be included to ensure NIH has the ability to spend the money as needed for the CRADA.',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,0,'admin','2015-01-05 15:36:31',NULL),(40,0,2,'Performance','',40,'default','IBM will provide funds in accordance with the performance of the Research Plan.  IBM will make payments according to payment schedule set forth below.   If IBM fails to m